org.firstinspires.ftc.teamcode

Class LibraryGyroDrive

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.firstinspires.ftc.teamcode.LibraryGyroDrive

  • public class LibraryGyroDrive
extends java.lang.Object
    This is our custom library that we use to drive forward. The point of using a gyro sensor is to drive straight using it reaches a certain position. If the robot runs over an object or hits something it will take the error of the robot and correct it to get back on track and continue driving forward

      • getError

        public double getError(double targetAngle)
        getError determines the error between the target angle and the robot's current heading
        Parameters:
        targetAngle - Desired angle (relative to global reference established at last Gyro Reset).
        Returns:
        error angle: Degrees in the range +/- 180. Centered on the robot's frame of reference +ve error means the robot should turn LEFT (CCW) to reduce error.

      • getSteer

        public double getSteer(double error,
                       double PCoeff)
        returns desired steering force. +/- 1 range. +ve = steer left
        Parameters:
        error - Error angle in robot relative degrees
        PCoeff - Proportional Gain Coefficient
        Returns:
